FBIS4-46348 "jptot024__l94025" JPRS-TOT-94-024-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 7 June 1994 EAST ASIA PHILIPPINES Abu Sayyaf Group Bomb Detonates in Zamboanga City Abu Sayyaf Group Bomb Detonates in Zamboanga City Abu Sayyaf Claims Responsibility BK0706044894 Quezon City Radio Filipinas in English 0230 GMT 7 Jun 94 BK0706044894 Quezon City Radio Filipinas English BFN [Text] The Abu Sayyaf extremist group has claimed responsibility for the Sunday bombing at the commercial center in Zamboanga City in southern Philippines. Xeroxed letters reportedly from a certain Abu Jihad were delivered by an unidentified youth yesterday afternoon. Thirty-six people were wounded in the bomb blast. The explosive was believed planted inside or beneath a car parked beside Shopper Central. The car was a total wreck. The explosion was so powerful, it was heard by residents within a five kilometer radius.
